BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:aw-ind-psp@awtrading
DTSTART:20260709T190000
DTEND:20260709T203000
SUMMARY:🛠️ INDICATOR — PSP (Precision Swing Point)
DESCRIPTION:Feature 5: PSP\n\nOn each confirmed bar:\n• If Symbol A closes bullish AND Symbol B closes bearish → Bearish PSP\n• If Symbol A closes bearish AND Symbol B closes bullish → Bullish PSP\n• Draw a label/shape on the chart\n• Default symbols: ES1! and NQ1!\n• Spec: src/indicator/indicator-spec.md\n\nAgent prompt:\n"Implement Feature 5 (PSP) from the spec. Use request.security() for Symbol B. Only fire on barstate.isconfirmed."
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:aw-ind-smt-core@awtrading
DTSTART:20260713T190000
DTEND:20260713T203000
SUMMARY:🛠️ INDICATOR — SMT Core (single pair)
DESCRIPTION:Feature 6: SMT — Smart Money Tool\n\nDetect swing divergence between chart symbol and one user-defined symbol:\n• Bearish SMT: chart makes higher swing high\, other makes lower swing high\n• Bullish SMT: chart makes lower swing low\, other makes higher swing low\n• Configurable swing lookback (default 5)\n• Draw label at divergence point\n• Spec: src/indicator/indicator-spec.md
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:aw-ind-smt-multipair@awtrading
DTSTART:20260716T190000
DTEND:20260716T210000
SUMMARY:🛠️ INDICATOR — Multi-Pair SMT (ES / YM / NQ) + SSMT
DESCRIPTION:Features 7 + 8: Multi-Pair SMT and SSMT Sequential\n\nExtend SMT to all three pairs:\n• ES vs NQ (default on)\n• ES vs YM\n• NQ vs YM\n• Confluence label when 2+ pairs fire same bar\n\nThen add SSMT:\n• Track last N SMT signals\n• If 2+ consecutive signals same direction → SSMT confirmed\n• Draw SSMT marker and optional connecting line\n• Spec: src/indicator/indicator-spec.md
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:aw-ind-qt@awtrading
DTSTART:20260720T190000
DTEND:20260720T210000
SUMMARY:🛠️ INDICATOR — QT (Quarterly Theory)
DESCRIPTION:Feature 9: Quarterly Theory overlay\n\nDivide the session into 4 equal quarters visually.\nFlag when SMT fires at or near a quarterly boundary (within N bars).\n• Off by default — user opts in\n• Draw subtle vertical lines at quarter boundaries\n• "QT SMT" label when SMT fires at boundary\n• Spec: src/indicator/indicator-spec.md\n\nNote: Coordinate with Daye's QT framework. Quarter boundaries are time-based\, not price-based.
END:VEVENT

